<TITLE> OMS rice sale starts Monday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 9 (bdnews24.com)  The government starts selling rice countrywide under its Open Market Sale (OMS) scheme from Monday to keep rice price within the reach during Ramadan. "Through the OMS programme 1.18 lakh metric tons of rice will be sold in 64 districts of the country. The programme will run through to October 11," acting food secretary Dhiraj Kumar Malakar Sunday told bdnews24.com. Food ministry sources said each kg of rice would be sold at Tk 19. Rice would be sold in open market every alternate day through 15,400 dealers and 500 BDR shops in the town areas. A family can buy a maximum of three kg rice at a time, they said. The dealers would buy rice from the government at Tk 18 a kg. bdnews24.c
